  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">National Initiatives for Sustainable &amp; Climate Smart oil Palm Smallholders Ghana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In 2020, implementation of the NI-SCOPS programme (National Initiatives on Sustainable and Climate Smart Oil Palm Smallholders) commenced in both Ghana and Nigeria. In Ghana, 6,634 (50%) project beneficiaries were profiled. There were 305,000 oil palm seedlings distributed, which translates to about 2,132 hectares. The baseline survey and methodology for KPI monitoring were established, in cooperation with the National Advisory Committee (NAC), ensuring the programme KPIs will be contributing to Ghana&#x2019;s Nationally Determined Contributions (NDCs).</narrative>
  </description>
